I'm not obligated to answer that.

67
00:04:56,045 --> 00:04:57,547
I want the truth.

68
00:04:57,630 --> 00:05:01,634
And I want the truth
to punish those who did wrong.

69
00:05:01,718 --> 00:05:03,761
So the victims
don't turn into perpetrators

70
00:05:06,597 --> 00:05:10,351
Just like the man who got framed
for arson after an unjust death,

71
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:11,811
Do Tae-hun.

72
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:19,694
If you're on Ms. Cha's side for revenge,

73
00:05:20,361 --> 00:05:22,322
remember this.

74
00:05:22,405 --> 00:05:25,158
Ms. Cha must already know that.

75
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,453
She gave you the case

76
00:05:28,536 --> 00:05:31,414
to use your resentment
towards the president-elect.

77
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:32,623
I don't care.

78
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:37,211
Because after getting revenge on him,

79
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:38,588
your next target is

80
00:05:39,172 --> 00:05:40,089
Ms. Cha?

81
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:44,594
Or are you planning to come between them

82
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:47,096
so the divorce suit ruins them both?

83
00:05:53,186 --> 00:05:55,688
Ms. Cha uses people.

84
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,648
She doesn't get used.

85
00:05:58,858 --> 00:06:00,068
Let me ask you again.

86
00:06:00,985 --> 00:06:02,070
What do you want?

87
00:06:10,953 --> 00:06:13,539
It's been about ten minutes.
My client's waiting.

88
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:16,042
We might want the same thing.

89
00:06:17,418 --> 00:06:19,378
If you really want revenge…

90
00:06:21,089 --> 00:06:23,758
If you really want a just punishment,

91
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:25,218
the answer is

92
00:06:25,301 --> 00:06:28,179
the special act, not the divorce suit.

93
00:06:28,262 --> 00:06:30,515
-Once the special act is passed--
-Hey, look.

94
00:06:32,266 --> 00:06:34,727
You don't know how awful hope is, do you?

95
00:06:34,811 --> 00:06:37,355
I've tried literally everything
for the past 15 years.

96
00:06:37,438 --> 00:06:40,358
I've protested, collected signatures
on the streets,

97
00:06:40,441 --> 00:06:42,985
everything I could
to get the special act passed.

98
00:06:43,486 --> 00:06:44,987
I was so desperate…

99
00:06:50,701 --> 00:06:52,370
that I even became a lawyer.

100
00:06:58,376 --> 00:07:00,378
There's this thing Ms. Cha has.

101
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:03,506
We can get the special act passed

102
00:07:04,215 --> 00:07:05,424
if you help me get it.

103
00:07:06,175 --> 00:07:07,009
A thing?

104
00:07:07,093 --> 00:07:08,427
Something that keeps

105
00:07:08,511 --> 00:07:10,763
the Party for Peace and Freedom
under control.

106
00:07:10,847 --> 00:07:15,101
Something like an audio tape
or an accounting ledger.

107
00:07:15,184 --> 00:07:16,811
-If you just--
-Steal it?

108
00:07:19,021 --> 00:07:20,898
You said you tried everything.

109
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:25,403
So why not try

110
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:28,698
one more thing?

111
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:39,625
Are you defying me?

112
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:42,545
Release U-yeong first.

113
00:07:43,045 --> 00:07:43,963
After that.

114
00:07:45,506 --> 00:07:47,049
So you don't trust me.

115
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:56,684
I've never had a dad.

116
00:07:58,478 --> 00:08:02,607
So I want to make sure
our child has a dad.

117
00:08:03,524 --> 00:08:04,442
"Our child"?

118
00:08:05,193 --> 00:08:07,069
You told me not to make it anxious.

119
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:10,990
It was thanks to you.

120
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,242
If I hadn't met you,

121
00:08:13,993 --> 00:08:15,620
my life would've been so boring.

122
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,842
The guy who got arrested

123
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:30,927
is the father?

124
00:08:31,010 --> 00:08:33,012
Release U-yeong first.

125
00:08:33,804 --> 00:08:35,306
Then I'll do whatever you say.

126
00:08:35,389 --> 00:08:37,016
What if I release him

127
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:39,894
and you still don't do as I say?

128
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:45,775
I haven't thought about it.

129
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:51,322
So you don't trust me either.

130
00:09:05,836 --> 00:09:08,631
LAWYER KANG SEON-HO

131
00:09:11,425 --> 00:09:13,844
The person you have reached
is unavailable.

132
00:09:13,928 --> 00:09:15,846
Please leave a message after the tone.

133
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:17,557
Additional charges may apply.

134
00:09:18,724 --> 00:09:19,976
It's me, Cha Su-yeon.

135
00:09:20,059 --> 00:09:23,938
You must be being questioned right now.
Come to my place as soon as you hear this.

136
00:09:24,647 --> 00:09:27,900
I need to have her sign a paper
agreeing to do as I say

137
00:09:27,984 --> 00:09:30,278
in exchange
for releasing the child's father.

138
00:09:31,195 --> 00:09:35,533
A legally binding document drafted
in the presence of a lawyer.

139
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:43,749
Once I sign the paper,

140
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,501
will you release U-yeong?

141
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,420
If we can't trust each other,

142
00:09:48,379 --> 00:09:50,214
we have to rely on the law.

143
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:51,924
We're good now?

144
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:05,104
The Special Act for
the Investigation of the H Chemical Fire

145
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:07,315
and the Establishment of a Safer Society,

146
00:10:07,398 --> 00:10:11,193
also known as the Do Tae-hun Special Act,
the vote on it is just a day away.

147
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:14,071
The Party for Peace and Freedom
has officially opposed the bill,

148
00:10:14,155 --> 00:10:16,949
breaking from
former Assemblywoman Bae's earlier pledge.

149
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:20,536
Let's hear from Noh Cheol-jae,
the floor leader of the party.

150
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,788
We've never changed our party's stance.

151
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:28,419
We just corrected the improper deal
former Assemblywoman Bae made

152
00:10:28,502 --> 00:10:30,504
in return for the prime minister position.

153
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:33,424
It hasn't been long
since the election ended.

154
00:10:33,507 --> 00:10:37,261
What we need to do now is
unite the divided people,

155
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:41,515
not divide the nation
by bringing up the special act

156
00:10:41,599 --> 00:10:43,267
and playing the blame game.

157
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,853
Tell me, how does that serve
our national interest?

158
00:10:46,604 --> 00:10:49,315
Will your party officially
oppose the special act?

159
00:10:50,399 --> 00:10:51,734
Well…

160
00:10:53,694 --> 00:10:56,280
We've got to do what we've got to do.

161
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:58,407
Although,

162
00:10:58,491 --> 00:11:01,952
there will be another meeting
before tomorrow's vote.

163
00:11:02,036 --> 00:11:03,245
That's it for today.

164
00:11:03,329 --> 00:11:05,206
-Sir.
-A quick word, please.

165
00:11:05,289 --> 00:11:07,333
There is growing attention on whether

166
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:10,628
the president-elect's
first campaign pledge will fall through.

167
00:11:15,257 --> 00:11:16,675
You did the best you could.

168
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,094
So,

169
00:11:19,136 --> 00:11:20,679
stop here.

170
00:11:24,558 --> 00:11:25,893
Ms. Cha left.

171
00:11:25,976 --> 00:11:27,019
But…

172
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,857
He's stuck in there for hours.

173
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:39,031
Secretary Shin.

174
00:11:45,121 --> 00:11:47,123
You can't just barge in here.

175
00:11:47,957 --> 00:11:49,542
Don't tell him about our call.

176
00:11:50,042 --> 00:11:52,211
Once he finds out, I'll be fired.

177
00:11:57,091 --> 00:11:58,342
This is Shin Hae-rin.

178
00:11:58,884 --> 00:12:00,886
I have something urgent to tell you.

179
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:08,310
I'm coming in.

180
00:12:26,162 --> 00:12:29,915
I heard that Chief Secretary Lim
proposed passing the special act.

181
00:12:32,042 --> 00:12:33,461
You're not supposed to know that.

182
00:12:33,544 --> 00:12:35,546
I heard it from Chief Secretary Lim.

183
00:12:35,629 --> 00:12:37,006
What else did he say?

184
00:12:37,840 --> 00:12:39,508
That you didn't accept the offer.

185
00:12:39,592 --> 00:12:41,719
Was that the urgent thing
you wanted to talk about?

186
00:12:41,802 --> 00:12:44,013
You wanted to ask me
why I didn't accept it?

187
00:12:44,096 --> 00:12:45,097
No.

188
00:12:45,681 --> 00:12:47,766
I will get the special act passed.

189
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:52,480
I'm not asking for help.

190
00:12:52,563 --> 00:12:54,231
I'm asking you to stay out of it.

191
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:55,149
Secretary Shin.

192
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:57,860
Please don't forget
why you started the divorce suit.

193
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,196
It was for the special act.

194
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,530
Not for Ms. Cha.

195
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:05,034
I thought it was President Yu
who was trying to stop it.

196
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:08,162
So I was trying to protect her from him.

197
00:13:08,245 --> 00:13:09,663
Now you know.

198
00:13:10,414 --> 00:13:13,417
Now you know that Ms. Cha is the one
who has been stopping it!

199
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:17,463
I need to check something first.

200
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:18,506
After that--

201
00:13:18,589 --> 00:13:21,008
The one trying to stop the investigation
must be behind the incident.

202
00:13:21,634 --> 00:13:23,052
Secretary Shin.

203
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,596
If Ms. Cha, who was trying to stop
the special act, is the culprit,

204
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:26,597
she must pay for it.

205
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:29,934
Only then can we prove
Do Tae-hun's innocence.

206
00:13:32,394 --> 00:13:33,562
You know

207
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:37,274
politics isn't that simple.

208
00:13:37,358 --> 00:13:38,359
I know.

209
00:13:39,276 --> 00:13:42,780
I also know you've never turned away
from a problem with such an excuse.

210
00:13:44,573 --> 00:13:46,158
Are you saying I have changed?

211
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:51,664
Maybe you have changed.

212
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:55,918
Please don't stop the special act
just to protect Ms. Cha.

213
00:13:56,835 --> 00:13:58,712
And please don't stop me.

214
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:10,975
I can bear everything else.

215
00:14:12,476 --> 00:14:15,271
But the 20 years that I have lived for you

216
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:18,065
going to waste…

217
00:14:19,024 --> 00:14:20,609
I can't bear that.

218
00:14:30,536 --> 00:14:32,538
My wife wants me
to give up on the special act.

219
00:14:34,415 --> 00:14:36,125
She said if I keep pushing it,

220
00:14:36,917 --> 00:14:38,752
she'd expose who I had an affair with.

221
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:41,297
Lee Hwa-jin?

222
00:14:45,175 --> 00:14:46,176
Did you know?

223
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,638
I did get a feeling
that she was getting the wrong idea.

224
00:14:50,389 --> 00:14:51,849
But it's not true.

225
00:14:51,932 --> 00:14:54,059
She says it doesn't matter if it's true

226
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:57,021
because Lee Hwa-jin will speak
to the press herself.

227
00:15:00,190 --> 00:15:01,817
She's going that far?

228
00:15:07,197 --> 00:15:08,532
You're right.

229
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:12,202
I've never avoided anything
because politics is complicated.

230
00:15:12,286 --> 00:15:15,247
But the problem I'm facing now
is extra complicated.

231
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:17,207
So give me some time.

232
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,920
Time to solve this problem.

233
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:24,590
We don't have time.

234
00:15:24,673 --> 00:15:26,216
We do, until the inauguration.

235
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,259
No.

236
00:15:28,344 --> 00:15:30,512
I'm not talking about your time.

237
00:15:32,181 --> 00:15:34,391
I'm talking about the time I have left.

238
00:15:38,228 --> 00:15:40,022
I made myself clear.

239
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:42,816
Don't stop the special act.

240
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:06,590
SPECIAL ACT

241
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:16,976
Secretary Shin!

242
00:16:17,059 --> 00:16:19,645
You think I'd just walk away quietly?

243
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:23,816
One word from me,
and you're done for, Hyun Min-cheol!

244
00:16:23,899 --> 00:16:27,403
Just imagine how many secrets
I know about you from the past 20 years.

245
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:30,280
And imagine what will happen
once I disclose them.

246
00:16:30,364 --> 00:16:31,865
You have no idea!

247
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:33,867
Have you lost your mind?

248
00:16:33,951 --> 00:16:36,328
You think you can just throw me out
and get away with it?

249
00:16:36,412 --> 00:16:37,913
Calm down. Let's talk outside.

250
00:16:37,997 --> 00:16:40,165
-Let go!
-Let's talk outside.

251
00:16:40,249 --> 00:16:43,085
-Let go.
-Come on. Talk with me.

252
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:06,108
Breaking news. Civil war has broken out.

253
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:08,110
Secretary Shin attacked
the president-elect.

254
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:10,863
She was cussing and yelling.
It was no joke.

255
00:17:10,946 --> 00:17:13,657
She was the top contributor.
I'm not surprised.

256
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:16,410
PARTICIPATION NATIONAL PARTY

257
00:17:17,286 --> 00:17:20,497
The alliance of parties other than
the Party for Peace and Freedom

258
00:17:20,581 --> 00:17:21,874
is already falling apart.

259
00:17:24,543 --> 00:17:28,422
No wonder. The divorce and the affair
ruined the president-elect's credibility.

260
00:17:29,089 --> 00:17:32,885
Some are already calling for
the president-elect to leave the party.

261
00:17:32,968 --> 00:17:35,721
If we push the special act too hard
and it fails,

262
00:17:35,804 --> 00:17:37,347
we'll take the blow too--

263
00:17:37,431 --> 00:17:39,475
Mr. Kwon, let's take a short recess.

264
00:17:40,851 --> 00:17:43,228
What is this?

265
00:17:44,271 --> 00:17:49,485
Sir, what are they saying? Secretary Shin
lashed out at the president-elect?

266
00:17:49,568 --> 00:17:50,861
The vote is tomorrow!

267
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:54,782
We're at war now. We can't afford
a civil war on top of that.

268
00:17:55,616 --> 00:17:56,825
Goodness!

269
00:17:56,909 --> 00:18:00,204
She's been the president-elect's
closest aide for the past 20 years.

270
00:18:00,287 --> 00:18:03,415
She deserves to be honored
for her contribution, not fired.

271
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:05,709
This isn't just about the president-elect!

272
00:18:05,793 --> 00:18:09,213
She's seen and heard everything
within our party about the election!

273
00:18:09,296 --> 00:18:11,423
What if she points the gun at us?

274
00:18:13,759 --> 00:18:15,844
Let's hear what she wants.

275
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:19,014
We have to ease her anger somehow.

276
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,685
Geez, what on earth…

277
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:35,114
Hello? Assemblyman Choi?

278
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:38,367
Hello, Secretary Shin. It's me.

279
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:39,910
So…

280
00:18:40,452 --> 00:18:42,287
I heard something upsetting happened.

281
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:44,790
Upsetting?

282
00:18:45,332 --> 00:18:47,334
It's not a personal matter like that.

283
00:18:47,835 --> 00:18:52,047
The party won't crumble just because
a low-ranking member like me leaves.

284
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:54,967
But if the special act gets thrown out,

285
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:58,178
our party's identity could be at stake.

286
00:18:58,262 --> 00:19:01,557
I just raised my voice a bit,
trying to be forthright with him.

287
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:05,185
I know. I know how loyal you are.

288
00:19:05,811 --> 00:19:08,355
I understand. I do.

289
00:19:08,438 --> 00:19:09,690
Speaking of which,

290
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:13,944
it seems like the Party for Peace
and Freedom will turn in favor of the act.

291
00:19:14,611 --> 00:19:18,866
As long as we keep our stance,
we'll easily get it passed.

292
00:19:22,327 --> 00:19:24,204
You must really like jjamppong.

293
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:26,165
You never go to barbecue restaurants.

294
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:31,003
I thought you knew that
I stopped going since the fire incident.

295
00:19:31,753 --> 00:19:32,754
Right.

296
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:34,381
Sorry.

297
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:36,383
I forgot. Goodness.

298
00:19:36,466 --> 00:19:38,218
Jjamppong is my comfort food.

299
00:19:38,802 --> 00:19:41,388
I don't need to worry
about who grills the meat.

300
00:19:42,181 --> 00:19:44,391
You do that every once in a while.

301
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:46,977
What about the source

302
00:19:48,187 --> 00:19:50,063
Cha Su-yeon promised to give us?

303
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:51,481
No news.

304
00:19:53,442 --> 00:19:55,402
But no news is good news, you know.

305
00:19:56,945 --> 00:19:59,406
To catch a big fish like this,

306
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:02,034
I need to be patient and wait.

307
00:20:02,117 --> 00:20:03,243
That's true.

308
00:20:04,828 --> 00:20:05,996
Right.

309
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:08,207
You heard
about the new program launch, right?

310
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:12,336
Looks like they're pushing it
as the main show.

311
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:13,879
I saw the budget and…

312
00:20:13,962 --> 00:20:15,797
Man, it was a lot.

313
00:20:19,384 --> 00:20:20,427
Speaking of which…

314
00:20:25,432 --> 00:20:28,268
What? Just say it.

315
00:20:30,854 --> 00:20:33,148
You're on the shortlist for the host.

316
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:38,403
Well, of course,

317
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:41,240
there are candidates from outside,
and even other networks,

318
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:42,950
so it'll be tough competition.

319
00:20:46,036 --> 00:20:47,204
But I'm betting on you.

320
00:20:49,831 --> 00:20:51,416
But don't go alone, okay?

321
00:20:51,500 --> 00:20:53,210
We've been working as a team.

322
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:55,587
Better the devil you know.

323
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:56,838
Why?

324
00:20:57,547 --> 00:20:59,967
Is being the team leader
for News Magazine not enough?

325
00:21:00,050 --> 00:21:01,093
Come on.

326
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:04,012
News Magazine is not my program.
It's yours.

327
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,598
And no one can replace you.

328
00:21:06,682 --> 00:21:07,766
So if you're going,

329
00:21:08,976 --> 00:21:09,977
take me with you.

330
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:13,939
Why me, though?

331
00:21:15,065 --> 00:21:19,319
With your people skills, convincing people
from outside or other networks

332
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:21,113
would be a piece of cake.

333
00:21:22,906 --> 00:21:24,616
I'm a loyal person.

334
00:21:25,534 --> 00:21:27,119
What is this really about?

335
00:21:28,912 --> 00:21:30,956
We hit a homer
with Cha's wiretapping story.

336
00:21:31,039 --> 00:21:34,001
Let's go for a back-to-back homer
with the president-elect's affair.

337
00:21:34,084 --> 00:21:35,544
Then the game's over.

338
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:38,755
Whoever's in the shortlist,
they won't be able to beat you.

339
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:43,051
Counting the chickens before they hatch,

340
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:45,095
I'm already getting full.

341
00:21:45,178 --> 00:21:46,888
Oh, come on.

342
00:21:46,972 --> 00:21:48,432
That's not what it is.

343
00:21:48,515 --> 00:21:52,227
The universe is sending
good energy your way.

344
00:21:52,936 --> 00:21:55,314
You know how intuitive I am.

345
00:22:02,029 --> 00:22:03,238
Oh, boy.

346
00:22:04,239 --> 00:22:06,908
Look who's calling.
Secretary Shin with no connections.

347
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:08,785
SHIN HAE-RIN

348
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:10,912
Sure.

349
00:22:12,205 --> 00:22:13,206
Hello?

350
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:15,542
I was going to call you.

351
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:17,836
I heard you quit.

352
00:22:17,919 --> 00:22:19,254
What happened?

353
00:22:21,131 --> 00:22:25,469
Right, that wasn't so nice of me then.
I didn't answer your calls.

354
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:30,640
You know presidential candidates
declare their assets.

355
00:22:31,141 --> 00:22:32,809
Who doesn't know that?

356
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:36,188
What? Will you report him
for breaking the election law?

357
00:22:37,397 --> 00:22:39,983
And if declared jewelry gets stolen,

358
00:22:40,067 --> 00:22:41,485
it's a criminal case, right?

359
00:22:41,568 --> 00:22:42,611
Yes, it is.

360
00:22:42,694 --> 00:22:46,490
A simple theft. Nothing more than
a single line in the news. Why do you ask?

361
00:22:48,116 --> 00:22:50,786
What if it's undeclared jewelry
that gets stolen?

362
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:54,831
That can be a little bigger case.

363
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:59,377
What if the undeclared jewelry
gets stolen,

364
00:22:59,878 --> 00:23:03,340
and you collude with the thief
to blackmail the president-elect?

365
00:23:04,049 --> 00:23:05,217
Wow.

366
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:09,096
Just hearing that excites me.

367
00:23:09,763 --> 00:23:11,264
Are you sure, though?

368
00:23:11,348 --> 00:23:14,184
Look into Seon U-yeong
arrested at Haseong Police Station.

369
00:23:14,267 --> 00:23:16,812
Haseong Police Station. Seon U-yeong.

370
00:23:16,895 --> 00:23:20,398
Are you sure about this?
I need to know for sure before I dive in.

371
00:23:20,482 --> 00:23:22,901
Kang Seon-ho is Seon U-yeong's lawyer.

372
00:23:22,984 --> 00:23:24,402
Cha Su-yeon's divorce lawyer?

373
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:29,991
Does this mean
Cha has Seon U-yeong's back?

374
00:23:30,659 --> 00:23:31,618
No.

375
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:36,248
She's using Seon U-yeong to join forces
with Lee Hwa-jin, her stylist.

376
00:23:36,915 --> 00:23:38,375
Her and Seon U-yeong are close.

377
00:23:39,292 --> 00:23:42,087
All right. Let me process this.

378
00:23:42,170 --> 00:23:43,630
That's all I can give you.

379
00:23:49,427 --> 00:23:52,556
Cheon is right
about the universe sending energy.

380
00:23:52,639 --> 00:23:54,683
This is my ticket to the new program.

381
00:23:54,766 --> 00:23:56,226
MBS REPORTER KIM YUN-JI

382
00:23:58,436 --> 00:23:59,563
Hi, Min-ju.

383
00:23:59,646 --> 00:24:02,399
See if there's a Seon U-yeong arrested
at Haseong Station.

384
00:24:02,482 --> 00:24:05,652
And write down everything that you hear.
I'll be right there.

385
00:24:05,735 --> 00:24:06,611
Hey!

386
00:24:11,741 --> 00:24:12,784
To MBS, please.

387
00:24:23,128 --> 00:24:25,547
That kind of paper has no legal power.

388
00:24:26,298 --> 00:24:28,383
If you get Seon U-yeong released,

389
00:24:29,801 --> 00:24:33,180
Lee Hwa-jin does anything you say?
What is this, a gift voucher?

390
00:24:33,263 --> 00:24:35,348
Just make it believable to her.

391
00:24:35,432 --> 00:24:36,766
That's what matters.

392
00:24:36,850 --> 00:24:39,644
I'll keep the promise anyway.

393
00:24:43,982 --> 00:24:46,067
Are you telling me to trick Lee Hwa-jin?

394
00:24:46,151 --> 00:24:48,069
It may look like tricking her,

395
00:24:49,029 --> 00:24:50,697
but the results will be the same.

396
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:54,701
Seon U-yeong will be released,
and the divorce case will be dropped.

397
00:24:58,872 --> 00:25:02,000
A petition is enough
to release Seon U-yeong.

398
00:25:03,835 --> 00:25:05,295
You didn't really

399
00:25:06,630 --> 00:25:08,048
listen to what I said.

400
00:25:09,883 --> 00:25:12,344
Stopping the divorce suit is the priority.

401
00:25:13,136 --> 00:25:15,096
Petition or whatever comes next.

402
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:17,432
The detention period will expire soon.

403
00:25:17,515 --> 00:25:19,017
Before the arrest warrant--

404
00:25:19,100 --> 00:25:21,770
Whether he's arrested or ends up in jail,

405
00:25:22,395 --> 00:25:23,521
I don't care.

406
00:25:25,357 --> 00:25:26,816
Mr. Kang.

407
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,361
Don't forget who you're working for.

408
00:25:31,279 --> 00:25:33,323
Until the divorce case is dropped,

409
00:25:33,406 --> 00:25:35,992
there will be no petition or release.

410
00:25:36,076 --> 00:25:39,204
Did the president-elect say
he'd withdraw the divorce suit?

411
00:25:39,287 --> 00:25:40,747
It's a matter of time.

412
00:25:41,915 --> 00:25:42,999
Just make sure

413
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:45,502
that she can rest assured.

414
00:25:49,089 --> 00:25:50,382
Yes, ma'am.

415
00:25:50,924 --> 00:25:53,468
I'll get going now.

416
00:25:57,514 --> 00:26:00,392
By the way, I didn't get to eat today.

417
00:26:01,226 --> 00:26:04,396
Before I go, can I have ramyeon
down in the kitchen?

418
00:26:06,314 --> 00:26:08,024
Ramyeon won't do.

419
00:26:08,108 --> 00:26:11,027
I'll have my butler prepare a meal.

420
00:26:13,863 --> 00:26:14,948
Hello?

421
00:26:15,031 --> 00:26:17,575
Could you prepare a meal for Lawyer Kang?

422
00:26:18,618 --> 00:26:20,704
And more tea for me.

423
00:26:20,787 --> 00:26:22,789
I want to get more rest.

424
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:25,041
Thanks.

425
00:26:27,419 --> 00:26:28,878
Anything more you want to say?

426
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:30,213
No.

427
00:26:31,381 --> 00:26:33,091
I'll go downstairs, then.

428
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:22,390
Let me know if you want more.

429
00:27:23,475 --> 00:27:24,476
Actually,

430
00:27:25,685 --> 00:27:27,937
I was just about to ask
for one more bowl of rice.

431
00:27:28,021 --> 00:27:30,982
My gosh, you must've been famished.

432
00:27:31,066 --> 00:27:33,193
That's three bowls of rice.

433
00:27:34,986 --> 00:27:36,821
Well, I had a lot of things

434
00:27:37,781 --> 00:27:39,449
to deal with today.

435
00:27:50,543 --> 00:27:52,253
Do you not

436
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:54,506
have a family?

437
00:27:55,715 --> 00:27:59,010
You're always here, you never go home.

438
00:27:59,094 --> 00:28:01,638
I've been doing this since I was 16.

439
00:28:01,721 --> 00:28:04,349
I never had time to make a family.

440
00:28:08,436 --> 00:28:09,479
But then,

441
00:28:10,063 --> 00:28:13,858
you've been with Ms. Cha for a long time.
She must be like family to you.

442
00:28:13,942 --> 00:28:16,945
Family? No way.

443
00:28:17,028 --> 00:28:20,073
She was the first person
to ever treat me like a human.

444
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:25,620
I used to be called a servant,

445
00:28:25,703 --> 00:28:28,623
but she gave me the title of butler.

446
00:28:30,959 --> 00:28:34,170
I didn't know
you were such a sociable person.

447
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:36,965
Oh, I apologize.

448
00:28:37,048 --> 00:28:38,174
I went overboard.

449
00:28:38,258 --> 00:28:40,677
No, I like it. It feels natural.

450
00:28:41,886 --> 00:28:43,430
You don't have to stand there.

451
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:46,683
Please do your thing.
I'll clean up after finishing it.

452
00:28:47,308 --> 00:28:49,018
No, you can just leave it there.

453
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:52,272
I'll go check on Ms. Cha.

454
00:28:52,355 --> 00:28:54,816
I just made some more tea for her.

455
00:28:54,899 --> 00:28:55,817
Okay.

456
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:11,249
No legal power?

457
00:29:11,332 --> 00:29:14,919
That's why I came here
before going to Ms. Cha's place.

458
00:29:15,003 --> 00:29:16,880
I thought you should know.

459
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:21,718
So she lied to me.

460
00:29:22,302 --> 00:29:23,678
But

461
00:29:23,762 --> 00:29:26,264
there's another way
to get U-yeong released.

462
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:30,477
Please tell me in detail
where and how you stole the necklace.

463
00:29:33,938 --> 00:29:35,648
Why do you ask that?

464
00:29:35,732 --> 00:29:39,194
I'm going to find Ms. Cha's weakness.

465
00:29:39,277 --> 00:29:40,403
Once I find it,

466
00:29:41,404 --> 00:29:42,655
I can

467
00:29:43,448 --> 00:29:44,949
help get U-yeong released.

468
00:29:47,535 --> 00:29:48,995
Trust me.

469
00:29:49,078 --> 00:29:51,623
I will get him out.

470
00:29:58,254 --> 00:30:00,381
I stole the necklace

471
00:30:00,465 --> 00:30:02,217
from the walk-in closet.

472
00:31:20,879 --> 00:31:22,422
Was it in a safe?

473
00:31:23,006 --> 00:31:26,259
No. It was in a display cabinet,
not a safe.

474
00:31:26,342 --> 00:31:29,220
I frequented the place,
so I knew where it was.

475
00:31:35,768 --> 00:31:37,061
Gosh, that scared me.

476
00:31:52,035 --> 00:31:54,996
And the cabinet isn't locked?

477
00:31:55,705 --> 00:31:56,623
It isn't.

478
00:31:56,706 --> 00:31:59,000
What about a safe? Was there no safe?

479
00:32:01,669 --> 00:32:03,963
Oh, I've seen it.

480
00:32:04,047 --> 00:32:05,757
A safe, in the dressing room.

481
00:32:06,966 --> 00:32:09,761
When I took out the necklace
from the cabinet,

482
00:32:09,844 --> 00:32:12,096
I saw a button under the shelf.

483
00:32:19,228 --> 00:32:21,731
When I pressed the button,
the wall slid open.

484
00:32:34,285 --> 00:32:36,996
Please enter your password.

485
00:32:42,043 --> 00:32:43,586
I need to know the password.

486
00:32:43,670 --> 00:32:46,923
Most of Ms. Cha's passwords,
including her phone,

487
00:32:47,006 --> 00:32:48,800
are 1119.

488
00:32:49,634 --> 00:32:51,177
Ji-yu's birthday.

489
00:33:01,354 --> 00:33:04,315
Wrong password.

490
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:05,650
Please try again.

